Interface TypedMap<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - Key
    V - Value.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Map<K,V>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    TempTypedMap<K,V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BackedTempTypedMap, BackedTypedMap, UnmodTypedMap

    public interface TypedMap<K,V>
extends java.util.Map<K,V>
    A map that stores a key and a value with a type. Keys are identified by the value type and the key itself, values can be get either by key and a pair of key and type. All values have a reified TypeInfo, make sure to insert correct types. Implementations are free to chose the way to store reified value type, but keys remains unique, this means that if the same key is associated to a different value or value type, the old key should be replaced.
    See Also:
    Map
